      <title>Our Place in the Nature of Things</title>
      <description>David McConville, media artist and director of the Worldviews Network joins me this week for a journey into the powers of human cognition and our capacity to know our universe, our place in it, and how our collective actions craft our future. Key to human thriving is our understanding of belonging, relationship, and interaction on all scales. Without this we remain fragmented, and we don’t fare well. In the Dagara tradition of West Africa they say our belonging is half of our identity, and without an experience of belonging there is no ‘home’ for the other half of our identity – our individual genius – to express its value or participate in evolving the world at a collective level. These are focal points for human consciousness – to experience high-level collective membership so individual creativity can contribute to the whole. The key for modern people is to risk the experience – it’s the path to regaining full consciousness – and experience is David McConville’s expertise. Join us!</description>
