      <description>Malachi Leopold, founder of Left Brain/Right Brain Productions, joins me this week for an in-depth look at the power of entrepreneurship done right. The world ‘entrepreneur’ means being between the give and take. It means being the central driver of value creation and value exchange. It is a dynamic engagement that is at once collective and at the same time requires entrepreneurs to be fully attuned to the deep story and meaning of the arena and relationships that comprise the environment of their business engagements. Looking good isn’t enough; clever slogans aren’t enough; the widget or service alone isn’t enough. It’s becoming very clear in business these days that true change leaders must finally merge their authentic personal and professional selves and become masters of conscious relationship and collaboration. This is full consciousness in action, and as Malachi Leopold tells us, we can address the world’s challenges through conscious entrepreneurship and innovation. Tune in!</description>
