      <title>Sufficiently Courageous!</title>
      <description>Join me this week for another engaging talk with Carol Dearborn, President of The Sufficiency Foundation. We’ll go beyond the concept of sufficiency into a discussion of value and authenticity. We are facing great challenges in the world today, and not all of them are being voiced. One of these challenges lies in our tendency to retreat into scarcity mentality, allowing ourselves to be guided by fear. Scarcity and fear are both hallmarks of isolated linear awareness; they rob us of our creative initiative and deplete what value we’ve generated. How do we find our way back to a state where we clearly perceive and generate life-enhancing value, instead of constantly giving up what we value most? To date, our approach has been verbal, and the limits of this are reflected back to us politically, financially, and socially. Talk is the currency of isolated awareness, and we need a new currency – a currency of authenticity, creativity, and courage to move beyond old ideas into new thriving.</description>
