      <title>Flames of Consciousness</title>
      <description>Burning Man: the mysterious annual desert project created by 50,000+ participants conjures visions of fiery Pagan cults, ragged dust-blown hippies, and wild freeform artists. The reality is ‘Burners’ are people consciously living a life of radical inclusion, self-reliance, civic responsibility, participatory culture, and immediacy. What makes Burning Man unique, and why would you want to travel to a hot, dry alkaline lake bed to witness a 40-foot tall wooden man explode into flames? Independent producer, designer, writer and business owner Geoff Puckett joins us to talk about his recent experience in Black Rock City, the once-a-year name of Nevada's 7th largest urban center. We’ll explore Burning Man's 10 Principles along with the very real, deeply emotional transformation attendees experience. You'll learn how living for a week in a realm absent of civilized masks, and full of genuine love, endless creative outlets, empowers consciousness and gives us new perspectives on our world.</description>
