      <title>A Lineage of Thriving</title>
      <description>Renee Baribeau, consultant, author, and founder of Desert Holistic Network, returns to Awakening Value™ to discuss the wisdom traditions and our need for lineage. In indigenous lineages, the knowledge needed for thriving is kept alive through a process called initiation – a multi-stage, guided process that begins with individual maturation, then the gifting of power and knowledge, followed by the initiate using that knowledge in service. Eventually, the initiate becomes the living embodiment of the culture’s wisdom, all the while stewarding its evolution. This is lineage. Young indigenous people now rush to be Western, to benefit from the new things we offer, but these things don’t include the wisdom of thriving. Today, in a globally connected world, we must realize that the wisdom of conscious thriving can’t be withheld or forgotten. It must be transmitted to evolve modern cultures. It is now our responsibility to become the lineage – the ones who remember and evolve ways to thrive.</description>
